        tags: ["Official", "College Board", "Curriculum", "Exam Info"],
        type: "DOCUMENT",
        status: "approved",
      },
      {
        title: "Flipping Physics - AP Physics C",
        description:
          "A comprehensive video series by Bill Fox, covering the entire AP Physics C curriculum with clear explanations, example problems, and real-world demonstrations. Highly recommended for visual learners.",
        url: "https://www.flippingphysics.com/ap-physics-c.html",
        tags: ["Video Series", "Review", "Mechanics", "E&M"],
        type: "VIDEO_SERIES",
        status: "approved",
      },
      {
        title: "AplusPhysics",
        description:
          "A website with tutorials, videos, and forums specifically for high school and AP physics. The AP Physics C section has notes, problem sets, and review materials.",
        url: "https://www.aplusphysics.com/courses/ap-c/AP_C_Physics.html",
        tags: ["Website", "Review", "Notes", "Problems"],
        type: "WEBSITE",
        status: "approved",
      },
      {
        title: "Dan Fullerton (YouTube)",
        description:
          "The creator of AplusPhysics also has a YouTube channel with lectures and problem-solving videos. His style is straightforward and focuses on the core concepts needed for the exam.",
        url: "https://www.youtube.com/user/FizziksGuy/playlists?view=50&sort=dd&shelf_id=7",
        tags: ["Video Series", "Lectures", "Problem Solving"],
        type: "VIDEO_SERIES",
        status: "approved",
      },
      {
        title: "MIT OpenCourseWare - Physics 8.01 (Mechanics)",
